---
import BaseHead from '../../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={`Staff - ${SITE_TITLE}`} description="Meet our staff" />
		<style>
			.staff-member {
				margin-bottom: 1em;
				border: 1px solid var(--silver);
				border-radius: 4px;
				overflow: hidden;
			}
			.staff-member summary {
				padding: 1em;
				cursor: pointer;
				list-style: none;
				user-select: none;
				display: flex;
				justify-content: space-between;
				align-items: center;
				background: var(--white);
				transition: background 0.2s;
			}
			.staff-member summary:hover {
				background: var(--silver);
			}
			.staff-member summary::marker {
				display: none;
			}
			.staff-member summary::-webkit-details-marker {
				display: none;
			}
			.staff-member summary::before {
				content: '+ ';
				display: inline-block;
				margin-right: 0.5em;
				font-weight: 700;
			}
			.staff-member[open] summary::before {
				content: '− ';
			}
			.staff-name {
				font-size: 1.2em;
				font-weight: 700;
				color: var(--deep-space-blue);
			}
			.staff-member .position {
				font-weight: 700;
				color: var(--sky-surge);
				font-size: 1em;
			}
			.staff-content {
				padding: 1em;
				background: var(--white);
			}
			.staff-content p {
				margin-bottom: 1em;
			}
		</style>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<h1>Staff</h1>
			
			<details class="staff-member">
				<summary>
					<span class="staff-name">Muzammal Afzal</span>
					<span class="position">Executive Director</span>
				</summary>
				<div class="staff-content">
					<p>Muzammal Afzal is the current Executive Director of Philly Jobs with Justice. Muzammal has dedicated their career to advancing the well-being and empowerment of marginalized communities. Their work is rooted in a deep commitment to socio-economic development, with a focus on worker organizing, community advocacy, and addressing structural inequalities.</p>
					<p>With a diverse professional background, Muzammal has previously served as the Program Manager for the Asian American Community Fund of PA, where they led initiatives that uplifted Asian American communities across Pennsylvania. Prior to that, they served as community organizer with the Asian Pacific Islander Political Alliance, working to amplify the voices of underrepresented populations in PA.</p>
					<p>Muzammal's academic credentials reflect profound dedication to understanding the intersections of economics, labor, and socio-economic justice. They hold an undergraduate degree in Economics, an MPhil in Economics, and a second master's in Labor and Global Workers' Rights—fields that inform both professional work and personal philosophy.</p>
					<p>Fluent in eight languages and well-versed in the diverse cultures of South Asia, Muzammal brings a rich cultural perspective to the labor movement. Their extensive experience spans community and labor organizing in both South Asia and the United States, where they have worked tirelessly to advance workers' rights and social change.</p>
					<p>Driven by a deep interest in philosophy and political theory, Muzammal continues to explore new ways to challenge and dismantle systems of injustice while fostering meaningful change in the communities they serve.</p>
				</div>
			</details>

			<details class="staff-member">
				<summary>
					<span class="staff-name">Nate Gosweiler</span>
					<span class="position">Worker Organizer</span>
				</summary>
				<div class="staff-content">
					<p>Nate is committed to the advancement of worker safety, dignity, and respect on the job. He helps workers build their capacity for collective action around workplace issues, overcome barriers created by employers, and assert their rights on the job. After participating in the Black Lives Matter protests in 2020, Nate turned away from a career in academia to join the labor movement. He believes that grassroots organizing must happen at the nexus of work and community and will change the status quo that is currently harming workers and their communities.</p>
				</div>
			</details>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>

